# Toolbox

## Structure
```
~/.toolbox/
├── bin/
│   └── toolbox           # Entry point (executable CLI)
├── lib/
│   ├── utils.sh          # Colors, icons, logging, help display
│   ├── create.sh         # Command: create
│   ├── read.sh           # Command: read
│   ├── delete.sh         # Command: delete
│   └── help.sh           # Command: help (optional)
└── toolbox.sh            # Dispatch logic for routing commands
```

## Usage

```bash
toolbox create
toolbox read <name>
toolbox delete <name>
toolbox help
```

## License

```
MIT
```

## Set up

In your `~/.bashrc` or `~/.zshrc`
```sh
export PATH="$HOME/.toolbox/bin:$PATH"
```
Then make it executable:
```sh
chmod +x ~/.toolbox/bin/toolbox
```

Then add these to your aliases:
```sh
# Toolbox
if [ -f ~/.toolbox/toolbox_aliases ]; then
    . ~/.toolbox/toolbox_aliases
fi
```

Finally, reload your shell:
```sh
source ~/.bashrc  # or `source ~/.zshrc`
```

---

## When adding new tools:
### REMEMBER: When adding new, be sure to:
- 1. Add to README.md
- 2. Add to help.sh
- 3. Add to toolbox.sh
- 4. Add to toolbox_aliases
